{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"dear-name-ladle","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run `rebar review-plan <ticket>` on a finding-rich, code-grounded ticket (its Pass-1\n   findings touch a code-grounding criterion -> Pass-2 takes the AGENTIC verify branch\n   `plan-review-verifier-agentic`).\n2. The agentic verifier re-grounds findings via tool calls and exceeds the step budget\n   (default `REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS=50`; runner: ~25 model requests / 50 tool calls).\n3. The verify workflow step raises: `step 'review@then/verify_branch@then/verify' failed:\n   agent exceeded its step budget (max_iterations=50; ...)`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- **Expected:** a verify step that can't complete should DEGRADE gracefully — the kernel\n  contract (`review_kernel.verify.verify_findings`) says un-verifiable findings route to\n  `pass3_decide(None)` -> per-finding INDETERMINATE, SURFACED, non-blocking; the review\n  still returns the Pass-1 findings. The gate's stated philosophy is fail-OPEN (\"anything\n  it cannot soundly check is skipped, never a false accusation\").\n- **Actual:** the step-budget error escapes to `gate_dispatch._run_plan_review`'s broad\n  fall-through (gate_dispatch.py ~131-134) -> `_degraded_plan_review_verdict` sets\n  `coverage.llm_unavailable=True` -> `finalize_verdict` returns a hollow **INDETERMINATE**\n  that DISCARDS all Pass-1 findings and is **unsigned**. Fail-CLOSED: an unsigned verdict\n  fails the plan-review claim gate, so a perfectly good plan **cannot be claimed**.\n\n## Evidence\n- Step 7 of threshold calibration: 3/20 reviews returned INDETERMINATE\n  (8e6f-3ad2-1f24-4b8b, 92fa-6657-3579-4043, 9df3-b461-9a06-49c0). All three sidecars:\n  `llm_ran=False`, `llm_unavailable=True`, identical `llm_error` = the verify step-budget\n  message. Not a size issue (these are ordinary stories; 92fa's Pass-1 even produced a\n  finding). The same run reviewed 17 other tickets fine with the same key/env.\n- Misclassification: \"verify step exceeded its agentic step budget\" is bucketed with\n  \"LLM unavailable / no API key / no [agents] extra,\" which is wrong — the LLM was up and\n  the finder ran.\n- Recovery gap: `_recover_plan_review_coach_failure` already recovers a Pass-4 COACH\n  failure (reconstructs the verdict from the decide partition). The analogous VERIFY\n  failure has no recovery -> falls through to the outage path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A Pass-2 verify-step failure (step-budget / transient / StructuredOutputError) no\n      longer sets `llm_unavailable` and no longer discards Pass-1 findings.\n- [ ] Such a review surfaces its Pass-1 findings (un-verifiable ones -> per-finding\n      INDETERMINATE, non-blocking) and does NOT fail the claim gate (fail-open), matching\n      the kernel `verify_findings` contract + the gate's documented fail-open posture.\n- [ ] Defense-in-depth: the agentic verifier's step budget is raised/scaled (e.g. with\n      finding count) so it trips far less often; documented.\n- [ ] A test reproduces the step-budget failure on the agentic verify branch and asserts\n      the verdict is NOT a hollow INDETERMINATE (findings preserved, claim not blocked).\n- [ ] (Investigate) whether the agentic verify branch over-triggers for tickets with no\n      code-grounding findings (8e6f/9df3 had none in history yet ran agentic verify).","id":"59bc-b9ba-021a-435f","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Plan-review verify-step budget exhaustion misclassified as llm_unavailable -> hollow INDETERMINATE blocks the claim"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782699487984350001,"uuid":"fc83e727-0441-4ad1-93d1-5e69efc0fec1"}